Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Combat aircraft of the North Atlantic Treaty 
Organization (NATO) shot down four military aircraft believed to 
be piloted by Serbs over Bosnia-Herzegovina. Asked by reporters 
in the Diet building on the morning of 1 March to comment on the 
incident, Prime Minister Hosokawa said: "NATO combat aircraft 
shot down the four military aircraft within the framework of the 
United Nations." In this way, the prime minister expressed his 
view that there was no problem with the action taken by NATO. 
  Commenting on the incident at a news conference on 1 March 
after a cabinet session, Chief Cabinet Secretary Takemura said, 
"I understand the action was taken in accordance with a 
resolution adopted by the UN Security Council." At the news 
conference, the government spokesman issued a statement saying: 
"Although it is not known to which side the downed military 
aircraft belonged, we hope that parties to the conflict will 
comply with the resolution adopted by the UN Security Council 
and work to end the conflict." 

